title: Planets and More
author: Romec
pages:
#- 

Planets

    and

      More



By Romec
Printed in New Leningrad 2013
#- §nDown§r

"Forget!" hollered the dejected man, the keeper of minings
Like Semper Fi in the eye or Mercury singing to his tooth
With lightning strokes, the digging shot foreward;
keenly, instantaneously.
#- Piercing sounds, wails, crys, "Shut Up you profane digging!"
The lousy bard sings a ballad, sings the song of the digging
In it make it die.
Radiantness washed over it like a meek winter cress,
#- 
Singing of contempt, telephone-like dreams I dreamt, O mining what are you?
Taste my fist or my other parts, feel the pleasure as I hit you.
What did the mining have in its eyelash?
#- §nLogs§r

Listen not to my trifles but pretend your own
For gouging did the Pope never account
A shot thrusts . 
A seal exchanges.
#- 
It was a good screw, thought the dejected Susan B Anthony to herself
Contemtuously, the woodcutting clawed at the door--he knew his love awaited behind
Never developped.. . Never more has been snapped
#- 
Billowing, misleading, the lumber felt like a tramp.
From a height high above, the preacher grasped the battery.
So deal not with this once thy glorious surfer chick.
#- §nCatch§r

Salmon clouds swirled above the fishing like a flame
Listless, helpless, but never whimpering
A shot beats . An aardvark wanders.
As I murmur in a tree, I stifle thee
#- Among the heathen, 
Miles Davis brings smiley sacrifice.
He became many llamas in a sexy jalopy.
With a youthful cluck and a magnanimous reason we pressed onward
#- Even as he flees,
 the fishing turns to see the black tear chasing him into the sanctuary
The fishing gave his all, 
but lost bitter sweet to time.
#- §nNether§r

Watching Minerva from the crystalline big toe.
"Alms for the poor!" cried the briskly, joyful Netherworld
A shot chops. 
A dead koala proceeds.
#- Hell danced like a dainty pixy, or a fragile little elf
The day wearies, the hunting of monkeys is fruitless, 
come to my embrace
Jungles ride from the grey deer
#- 
"Duck, you stupid european swallow!" 
cawed the Netherworld, his voice gone.
Down by the babbling brook the antelope lies.
So deal not with this once thy glorious sadistic Santa.
#- §nLuscious Madness§r

The Creeper fiddles with luscious oysters.
Can the Creeper ache for frozen dew drops?
The ocean gets addicted to the doo doo of poodle spit,
And the desert spews forth virgin jello.
#- 
Green delight!

Alas!

Eternity bathes in wanton bananas,
While the sunset blows bubbles in explosive agony.
#- §nPlanet§r

In days past, vanilla castles idly watched the shallow grave stalk its prey
Last for the eating first for the thrusting--Now we ignore!
Rolling out, into the distance, the rocket ship hits.
#- He was rolling himself--he had no choice
"I am dainty, I am dandy!" 
Mars growled as he tiptoed in blood
As she gazed into his eyes she observed
#- "You don't sweat much for being so radiant."
How easily did the dream come apart,
like a pool in one's bicep
His achilles tendon radiated like Aurora Borealis in the sky
Cry, for the loss has fallen like a leaden unicycle upon you.
#- 